    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/plaid/a7470e5b-2761-4251-9a59-a52c0f7c0e90/application",
    "company": "Plaid",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "cd029bd217c76056",
    "department": "Business Operations",
    "description": "We believe that the way people interact with their finances will drastically improve in the next few years. We’re dedicated to empowering this transformation by building the tools and experiences that thousands of developers use to create their own products. Plaid powers the tools millions of people rely on to live a healthier financial life. We work with thousands of companies like Venmo, SoFi, several of the Fortune 500, and many of the largest banks to make it easy for people to connect their financial accounts to the apps and services they want to use. Plaid’s network covers 12,000 financial institutions across the US, Canada, UK and Europe. Founded in 2013, the company is headquartered in San Francisco with offices in New York, Washington D.C., London and Amsterdam.\n\n\n\n\nProduct at Plaid builds the systems that power open finance for millions of developers and businesses. We are responsible for defining what we build, why we build it, and how we deliver it with excellence. This is a founding Product Operations role. It will report to the Head of Business Operations, who reports directly to Plaid’s founder and CEO. As we scale into a multi-product company, we are investing in strengthening how Product operates — ensuring clarity of priorities, consistent execution, and high-quality product work.\n\n\n\n\nAs our founding Product Operations Lead, you will define and own the operational backbone of the Product organization. You will work closely with Product, Engineering, Design, and Product Marketing to build the systems, cadences, and standards that help teams execute consistently and at high quality . You are a hands-on builder who enjoys operating from first principles and defining long-term strategy for your domain .\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n - \n\n - Own and evolve the operating system used by Product to plan, track, and communicate work, including roadmaps, planning artifacts, and execution tracking (in close partnership with Engineering Operations).\n\n - Design and run lightweight operating cadences (e.g., planning cycles, product reviews, execution check-ins)\n\n - Improve visibility into priorities, progress, and decisions across the product organization without adding unnecessary process\n\n - Define and own the PM tool stack, evolving the tools and workflows that PMs use every day to ensure the function is operating effectively\n\n - Identify where automation, AI/agents, and other new workflows can materially change how product work gets done, and translate those ideas into adopted capabilities.\n\n - Partner with Product leadership to reinforce a high-performing product culture, both virtually (e.g., Product All Hands) and in-person (e.g., Bi-Annual Product Summits / Onsites)\n\n - Build systems that capture and share high-quality product work (e.g., great PRDs)  and decisions across teams, helping raise the bar and accelerate learning.\n\n - Longer-term, own Product Manager onboarding and ongoing enablement, ensuring PMs ramp quickly and understand how great product work gets done at Plaid.\n\nQualifications:\n\n - \n\n - 8+ years of experience in Product Operations, Program Management, or a similar role.\n\n - Experience in fast-moving, product-led organizations with limited tolerance for unnecessary process.\n\n - Strong systems thinker who can design operating models that scale without adding bureaucracy.\n\n - Proven scrappy executor who takes ownership and gets things done.\n\n - Comfort operating in ambiguity and building from a blank page.\n\n - Clear, concise communicator with strong written and verbal skills.\n\n - Strong product instincts and empathy for Product Managers and cross-functional partners.\n\n - Prior technical experience and/or the curiosity to build a deep understanding of Plaid’s products\n\nOur mission at Plaid is to unlock financial freedom for everyone. To support that mission, we seek to build a diverse team of driven individuals who care deeply about making the financial ecosystem more equitable. We recognize that strong qualifications can come from both prior work experiences and lived experiences. We encourage you to apply to a role even if your experience doesn't fully match the job description. We are always looking for team members that will bring something unique to Plaid!\n\n\n\n\nPlaid is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and values diversity at our company. We do not discriminate based on race, color, national origin, ethnicity, religion or religious belief, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender, gender identity, gender expression, transgender status, sexual stereotypes, age, military or veteran status, disability, or other applicable legally protected characteristics. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state, and local laws. Plaid is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for candidates with disabilities in our recruiting process. If you need any assistance with your application or interviews due to a disability, please let us know at accommodations@plaid.com.\n\n\n\n\nPlease review our Candidate Privacy Notice here https://plaid.com/legal/#candidate-privacy-notice.",
